The Big Bang to the Blue Ridge

  • The universe began 13.8 billion years ago.

  • Appalchian Mtns: Formed over billion years ago

    • among Earth’s oldest mountain ranges
    • formation from the collision of ancient landmasses
    • major uplift/folding occurred during Pangea (335mya)

  • Erosion & Rejuvenation: Once as tall as the Alps, eroded to plains, then uplifted again in the Cenozoic

  • Ongoing Evolution: Continues to be shaped by erosion, weathering, and geological forces

Evolution in the Mountains

  • Early human migration: Paleo-Indians over 12,000 years ago.
  • Rich biodiversity shaped early life.
  • Communities evolved through contact, adaptation, isolation.

Human Adaptability in Appalachia

  • Mountain terrain → subsistence farming, barter economy.
  • Cultural resilience amid hardship and extraction.
  • Responding to environmental change.
